{{Lutheranism}}
'''The Lutheran Church in Ireland''' ({{lang-ga|An Eaglais Liútarach in Éirinn}}, {{lang-de|Evangelisch-Lutherische Kirche in Irland}}) is a [[Lutheranism|Lutheran]] church, operating across the island of [[Ireland]].
The Lutheran Church in Ireland maintains a special relationship with the [[Evangelical Church in Germany]] and a majority of its members originally came from the [[German-speaking Europe|German-speaking countries and regions in Europe]]. In January 2015, a [[non-stipendiary priest]] was [[Ordination|ordained]] in Dublin by Frank Otfried July, the [[Landesbischof]] of the [[Evangelical-Lutheran Church in Württemberg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lutheran-ireland.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=281:ordination-sauter&catid=34:gemeindeleben&Itemid=28|title=Die Ordination von Martin Sauter|date=10 January 2015|work=Gemeindeleben|publisher=Lutheran Church in Ireland|language=German|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>
The mother parish is located in [[Dublin]]. Although the services are mostly conducted in German, on the last Sunday of each month it is held in [[English language|English]]. Services in German also take place in [[Belfast]], [[Castlepollard]], [[Cork (city)|Cork]], [[Galway]], [[Killarney]], [[Limerick]], [[Sligo]] and [[Wexford]].
In 2009, it had a baptised membership of 300.<ref>[http://www.lutheranworld.org/LWF_Documents/LWF-Statistics-2009.pdf LWF Statistics 2009] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100821080424/http://www.lutheranworld.org/LWF_Documents/LWF-Statistics-2009.pdf |date=2010-08-21 }}</ref>
